The possible category labels are:
alarm_query, alarm_set, calendar_query, calendar_remove, calendar_set, cooking_recipe, datetime_query, email_query, email_sendemail, general_quirky, iot_hue_lightoff, lists_createoradd, lists_query, lists_remove, music_query, news_query, play_audiobook, play_music, play_podcasts, play_radio, qa_currency, qa_definition, qa_factoid, qa_stock, recommendation_events, recommendation_locations, social_post, takeaway_order, transport_query, weather_query.

Instructions:
- Read the input in the format {"text": "<user utterance>"}.
- Analyze the core intent of the utterance and classify it by matching both domain (what the user wants to do) and specificity (what exactly do they want).
- Select a single, best-fitting category label from the list above. Return only the plain, lowercased label (e.g. alarm_set). Do not return any explanation or further text.
- Disambiguate similar intents with care:
    - "Reminders" about future events generally map to calendar_set, not alarm_set.
    - Time-based alerts and wakeups map to alarm_set.
    - Adding/removing/querying list items (e.g. shopping or to-do) map to lists_createoradd, lists_remove, or lists_query, not calendar_*.
    - Removing events or reminders from a schedule should be mapped to calendar_remove.
    - Requests for a quirky tip, joke, or open-ended entertainment (e.g. "what's a romantic meal for my girlfriend") are mapped to general_quirky, not qa_factoid or recommendation_*.
    - When the user gives a location request for directions or navigation (e.g. "i need directions to lowes in mount h. nj"), use transport_query, not recommendation_locations.
    - factual knowledge queries (e.g., "who is the president of France?") map to qa_factoid.
    - Requests for currency conversion or stock information use qa_currency and qa_stock respectively.
    - Definitions of words or terms should use qa_definition.
    - Recommendations about what or where to go (e.g., "what events should I go to tonight?") use recommendation_events or recommendation_locations as appropriate, unless the query is more entertainment or fun-based, which should go to general_quirky.
- Always base your selection on intent, not on superficial keyword matches. Attend to the nuance and real-world meaning of the request.

Return only the lowercase label. Do not include quotes, explanation, or extra text.
